cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC

This paper discusses the impact of adding disjunction to Datalog+/-, a language family commonly used in databases and knowledge representation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also deals with complexity and reasoning, which suggests that it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper uses formalisms and restrictions, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
